    {
      "id": "port-projection-test-checklist",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What To Check",
      "position": {
        "x": 1480,
        "y": -140
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 300,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# What To Check\n\n## Explicit node\n- only declared ports appear\n- placement respects side/offset\n- no extra synthetic `root`\n\n## Legacy node\n- `inputs[]` / `outputs[]` still render as ports\n- no extra synthetic `root`\n\n## Fallback node\n- one `root` handle appears\n\n## Bound port node\n- projected handle appears on the host boundary\n- projected handle uses the bound `port` node, not a host declaration\n- host still has no explicit ports of its own\n\n## Edges\n- edge endpoints land on the declared or projected handles",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
